Source: duckbotos-meta
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Maintainer: DuckBotOS Team <duckets@duckbotos.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: duckbotos-mode-hermes
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: duckbotos-base,
         duckbotos-lm-studio,
         duckbotos-browseros,
         duckbotos-computer-use,
         duckbotos-cua-bridge,
         duckbotos-kiosk,
         duckbotos-kiosk-hermes,
         duckbotos-brain,
         duckbotos-hermes,
         python3-pip, python3-venv, python3-yaml, python3-requests,
         curl, wget, git,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: DuckBotOS Hermes-only install mode
 Installs Hermes (NousResearch) as the primary agent with the full DuckBotOS
 stack: Hermes agent, web dashboard, LM Studio, BrowserOS,
 Newest Desktop Control (computer-use), trycua/cua bridge, Weston kiosk shell,
 duckbot-rag-memory brain (default), and the Hermes kiosk configuration.
 .
 This is the "Hermes-only" install mode (DUCKBOTOS_MODE=hermes).
Choose this if you want a single-agent focused experience.

Package: duckbotos-mode-openclaw
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: duckbotos-base,
         duckbotos-lm-studio,
         duckbotos-browseros,
         duckbotos-computer-use,
         duckbotos-cua-bridge,
         duckbotos-kiosk,
         duckbotos-brain,
         duckbotos-openclaw,
         nodejs, npm,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: DuckBotOS OpenClaw-only install mode
 Installs OpenClaw as the primary agent with the full DuckBotOS stack:
 OpenClaw gateway, openclaw-os plugin, LM Studio, BrowserOS,
 Newest Desktop Control (computer-use), trycua/cua bridge, Weston kiosk shell,
 and duckbot-rag-memory brain (default).
 .
 This is the "OpenClaw-only" install mode (DUCKBOTOS_MODE=openclaw).
Choose this if you want OpenClaw as your primary desktop agent.

Package: duckbotos-mode-hybrid
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: duckbotos-base,
         duckbotos-lm-studio,
         duckbotos-browseros,
         duckbotos-computer-use,
         duckbotos-cua-bridge,
         duckbotos-kiosk,
         duckbotos-brain,
         duckbotos-hermes,
         duckbotos-openclaw,
         duckbotos-session-picker,
         gdm3, gnome-session,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: DuckBotOS hybrid install mode (Hermes + OpenClaw)
 Installs both Hermes and OpenClaw with the DuckBotOS session picker.
 At boot, users see a choice between:
 .
   [1] Hermes    — Fullscreen kiosk with Hermes Web Dashboard
   [2] OpenClaw  — Fullscreen kiosk with OpenClaw workspace
   [3] Hybrid    — GNOME desktop with both agents in a side panel
 .
 This is the most feature-complete DuckBotOS experience (DUCKBOTOS_MODE=hybrid).
 Both agents are always running; you pick which interface to use per-session.

Package: duckbotos-meta
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: duckbotos-mode-hermes
Description: DuckBotOS default meta-package (Hermes mode)
 Default DuckBotOS installation. Pulls in Hermes mode by default.
 To install OpenClaw or Hybrid mode, install duckbotos-mode-openclaw
 or duckbotos-mode-hybrid instead.
 Conflicts: duckbotos-mode-openclaw, duckbotos-mode-hybrid
Suggests: duckbotos-docs
